{
  "text": "Increased prevalence of CVD risk factors may be responsible for the excess mortality risk observed among blacks when compared to whites. For example, in the state economic areas surrounding the Atherosclerosis Risk in Communities (ARIC) study communities, blacks were shown to have higher blood pressure and glucose levels and a higher prevalence of obesity and diabetes. [CITATION_1] The authors also reported finding a greater clustering of risk factors among blacks.",
